  "prompt": "What is the main function of the brachiocephalic artery?",
  "response": "The main function of the brachiocephalic artery is to supply blood to the upper part of the body, specifically the right arm and the head and neck. It is a major artery that branches from the aorta and bifurcates into the right subclavian artery and the right carotid artery. These branches ensure that oxygenated blood reaches the right arm and the brain, face, and neck regions.",
